com.camerontec.catalys.fixtesttool.catalysserver

Class InProcessCatalysServerRunner

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.fixtesttool.catalysserver.InProcessCatalysServerRunner
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CatalysServerRunner

    public final class InProcessCatalysServerRunner
extends Object
    Class for running the Catalys Server inside the current process in a dedicated thread.

    The caller may optionally supply the ID of a component inside the Catalys Server to monitor for completion. If that component can be located and it implements BooleanOperationCompletionMonitor, the runner awaits explicit notification regarding completion.

        configFileName - The Catalys Server configuration file. Must not be null.
        applicationId - The application ID of the configured application (as per the configuration file). Must not be null.
        completionComponentId - The name of the component used to signal completion of the underlying operation. Must not be null. The component must implement BooleanOperationCompletionMonitor.
        completionTimeoutInMillis - The timeout in milliseconds for the underlying operation.
        deleteLogFileOnExit - True to delete the Catalys Server's default log file on exit, false to leave it in place.
        isClasspathConfig - if true, configFileName is expected to be available on the application's classpath. If false, it is expected to be an absolute path.
